cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of learning compact binary codes for image retrieval using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel pairwise loss function and an efficient parameter learning algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it focuses on image retrieval. Finally, the paper proposes an end-to-end deep hashing approach, which involves training a neural network to produce binary codes directly from image pixels without human intervention, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
